reviews.text: The staff there are very nice. However, trains are so often delayed, and when they do arrive, they are so full that nobody can get on. Its not a good service to leeds and it's got worse in  recent weeks.

Very small train station with 2 platforms and disabled ♿ access to both platforms, doesn't have a proper covered waiting area. There's only a hard metal where u can rest your bum, but freezing in cold wether. There's no parking space or bike rack, no toilet. Doesn't get crowded and delays are due to other train stations not from here. With a ticket machine you can get your tickets when there's no body to sell. Enjoy your trips everyone.
Ticket machine is handy on the platform. Step and step-free access is great
Ticket machine on platform.  Sometimes out of order but station is often manned so not too much of a problem.
